getMemberInfo(address,address).details: This function **must** be kept up to date with the Web3 UI when making changes. All PRs that change this function **must** be coordinated with an engineer on the Web3 Dashboard.

params.memberAddress: The address of the member whose info is being queried

params.metadataKey: The string that is the key of the metadata to look up

getSyndicateFeeAddress().details: This function is needed to allow inheriting contracts to only be able to view but not change syndicateFeeAddress without going through ownerSetSyndicateFeeAddress

getSyndicateValues(address).details: This function **must** be kept up to date with the web3 UI when making changes. All PRs that change this function or the SyndicateValues struct **must** be coordinated with an engineer on the Web3 Dashboard.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.feeAddress: The owner's new contract fee address

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
